# Import libraries

import pandas as pd

import seaborn as sns

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt



# Load data files (ensure path is correct or files are in the same directory as your notebook)

bm_df = pd.read_csv('BM_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

kidney_df = pd.read_csv('Kidney_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

liver_df = pd.read_csv('Liver_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

lung_df = pd.read_csv('Lung_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

ovary_df = pd.read_csv('Ovary_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

spleen_df = pd.read_csv('Spleen_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')



# Define the gene name you are interested in

target_gene = 'Zfp36l2'



# Extract TPM information for Zfp36L2

tissues = ['Bone Marrow', 'Kidney', 'Liver', 'Lung', 'Ovary', 'Spleen']

dfs = [bm_df, kidney_df, liver_df, lung_df, ovary_df, spleen_df]



expression_data = []



for tissue, df in zip(tissues, dfs):

    gene_data = df[df['Gene.name'] == target_gene]

    if not gene_data.empty:

        ko_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'KO' in col]

        wt_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'WT' in col]

        

        for col in ko_columns:

            expression_data.append({

                'Tissue': tissue,

                'Condition': 'KO',

                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]

            })

        

        for col in wt_columns:

            expression_data.append({

                'Tissue': tissue,

                'Condition': 'WT',

                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]

            })

    else:

        print(f"{target_gene} not found in {tissue}")



expression_df = pd.DataFrame(expression_data)



# Combine Tissue and Condition into a single column for better x-axis separation

expression_df['Tissue_Condition'] = expression_df['Tissue'] + ' (' + expression_df['Condition'] + ')'



# Plotting boxplot with jitter

plt.figure(figsize=(18, 8))

sns.boxplot(data=expression_df, x='Tissue_Condition', y='TPM', palette="Set3")

sns.stripplot(data=expression_df, x='Tissue_Condition', y='TPM', color=".25", jitter=True)



# Customize plot

plt.title('Expression of Zfp36l2 in WT and KO across Tissues')

plt.ylabel('TPM')

plt.xlabel('Tissue (Condition)')

sns.despine()



# Show plot

plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

# Import libraries
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind

# Set the context for the seaborn plot
sns.set_context("notebook", font_scale=1.25)

# Load data files
print("Loading data files...")
bm_df = pd.read_csv('BM_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
kidney_df = pd.read_csv('Kidney_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
liver_df = pd.read_csv('Liver_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
lung_df = pd.read_csv('Lung_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
ovary_df = pd.read_csv('Ovary_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
spleen_df = pd.read_csv('Spleen_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
print("Data files loaded successfully.")

# Define the gene name you are interested in
target_gene = 'Zfp36l2'

# Define tissues and associated data
tissues = ['Bone Marrow', 'Kidney', 'Liver', 'Lung', 'Ovary', 'Spleen']
dfs = [bm_df, kidney_df, liver_df, lung_df, ovary_df, spleen_df]

# Extract TPM information for Zfp36l2 and calculate differences
print("Extracting TPM information and calculating differences...")
expression_data = []
diffs = []
p_values = {}

for tissue, df in zip(tissues, dfs):
    gene_data = df[df['Gene.name'] == target_gene]
    if not gene_data.empty:
        ko_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'KO' in col]
        wt_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'WT' in col]

        for col in ko_columns:
            expression_data.append({
                'Tissue': tissue,
                'Condition': 'KO',
                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]
            })

        for col in wt_columns:
            expression_data.append({
                'Tissue': tissue,
                'Condition': 'WT',
                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]
            })

        # Calculate p-value between WT and KO
        ko_values = gene_data[ko_columns].values.flatten()
        wt_values = gene_data[wt_columns].values.flatten()
        t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(wt_values, ko_values, equal_var=False)
        p_values[tissue] = p_value

        # Calculate mean difference for sorting
        mean_diff = abs(ko_values.mean() - wt_values.mean())
        diffs.append((tissue, mean_diff))
    else:
        print(f"{target_gene} not found in {tissue}")

# Sort tissues based on the absolute differences in TPM
sorted_tissues = [tissue for tissue, diff in sorted(diffs, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)]
sorted_expression_data = sorted(expression_data, key=lambda x: sorted_tissues.index(x['Tissue']))

# Convert sorted data to DataFrame
print("Sorting data and preparing for plotting...")
sorted_expression_df = pd.DataFrame(sorted_expression_data)
sorted_expression_df['Tissue_Condition'] = sorted_expression_df['Tissue'] + ' (' + sorted_expression_df['Condition'] + ')'

# Define colors for WT and KO in sorted order
sorted_palette = {}
for tissue in sorted_tissues:
    sorted_palette[f'{tissue} (WT)'] = 'green'
    sorted_palette[f'{tissue} (KO)'] = 'purple'

# Plotting boxplot with jitter using sorted tissues
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
boxplot = sns.boxplot(data=sorted_expression_df, x='Tissue_Condition', y='TPM', palette=sorted_palette)
sns.stripplot(data=sorted_expression_df, x='Tissue_Condition', y='TPM', color=".25", jitter=True)

# Customize plot
plt.title(f'Expression of {target_gene} in WT and KO across Tissues (Sorted by TPM Difference)')
plt.ylabel('TPM')
plt.xlabel('Tissue (Condition)')
sns.despine()

# Create custom legend
handles = [
    plt.Line2D([0], [0], color='green', marker='o', linestyle='', label='WT'),
    plt.Line2D([0], [0], color='purple', marker='o', linestyle='', label='KO')
]
plt.legend(title='Condition', handles=handles)

# Function to add p-value annotations
def add_p_val_annotation(ax, x1, x2, y, p_val, h=0.02):
    """
    Adds p-value annotation to a plot.
    """
    p_text = f'p = {p_val:.2e}'
    ax.plot([x1, x1, x2, x2], [y, y+h, y+h, y], color='k')
    ax.text((x1 + x2) * .5, y + h, p_text, ha='center', va='bottom', color='k')

# Add p-values to the plot
positions = boxplot.get_xticks()
position_map = {group: pos for group, pos in zip(sorted_expression_df['Tissue_Condition'].unique(), positions)}
grouped = sorted_expression_df.groupby('Tissue')

for tissue, group in grouped:
    wt_pos = position_map[f'{tissue} (WT)']
    ko_pos = position_map[f'{tissue} (KO)']
    max_height = max(group['TPM'])
    add_p_val_annotation(boxplot, wt_pos, ko_pos, max_height, p_values[tissue], h=max_height*0.1)

# Show plot
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Save as SVG file
plt.savefig('Zfp36l2_expression_across_tissues_sorted.svg')
plt.show()

print("Plot saved as 'Zfp36l2_expression_across_tissues_sorted.svg' and displayed successfully.")

# Load data files
print("Loading data files...")
bm_df = pd.read_csv('BM_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
kidney_df = pd.read_csv('Kidney_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
liver_df = pd.read_csv('Liver_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
lung_df = pd.read_csv('Lung_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
ovary_df = pd.read_csv('Ovary_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
spleen_df = pd.read_csv('Spleen_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

dfs = [bm_df, kidney_df, liver_df, lung_df, ovary_df, spleen_df]

# Extract TPM information for Zfp36l2 and calculate differences
print("Extracting TPM information and calculating differences...")
expression_data = []
diffs = []

        wt_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'WT' in col]

                'Condition': 'KO',
                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]
            })

        for col in wt_columns:
            expression_data.append({
                'Tissue': tissue,
                'Condition': 'WT',
                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]
            })

        # Calculate p-value between WT and KO
        ko_values = gene_data[ko_columns].values.flatten()
        wt_values = gene_data[wt_columns].values.flatten()
        t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(wt_values, ko_values, equal_var=False)
        p_values[tissue] = p_value

        # Calculate mean difference for sorting
        mean_diff = abs(ko_values.mean() - wt_values.mean())

# Import libraries
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind

# Set the context for the seaborn plot
sns.set_context("talk", font_scale=1.5)  # Use larger font for publication

# Load data files
print("Loading data files...")
bm_df = pd.read_csv('BM_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
kidney_df = pd.read_csv('Kidney_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
liver_df = pd.read_csv('Liver_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
lung_df = pd.read_csv('Lung_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
ovary_df = pd.read_csv('Ovary_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
spleen_df = pd.read_csv('Spleen_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')
print("Data files loaded successfully.")

# Define the gene name you are interested in
target_gene = 'Zfp36l2'

# Define tissues and associated data
tissues = ['Bone Marrow', 'Kidney', 'Liver', 'Lung', 'Ovary', 'Spleen']
dfs = [bm_df, kidney_df, liver_df, lung_df, ovary_df, spleen_df]

# Extract TPM information for Zfp36l2 and calculate differences
print("Extracting TPM information and calculating differences...")
expression_data = []
diffs = []
p_values = {}

for tissue, df in zip(tissues, dfs):
    gene_data = df[df['Gene.name'] == target_gene]
    if not gene_data.empty:
        ko_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'KO' in col]
        wt_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'WT' in col]

        for col in ko_columns:
            expression_data.append({
                'Tissue': tissue,
                'Condition': 'KO',
                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]
            })

        for col in wt_columns:
            expression_data.append({
                'Tissue': tissue,
                'Condition': 'WT',
                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]
            })

        # Calculate p-value between WT and KO
        ko_values = gene_data[ko_columns].values.flatten()
        wt_values = gene_data[wt_columns].values.flatten()
        t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(wt_values, ko_values, equal_var=False)
        p_values[tissue] = p_value

        # Calculate mean difference for sorting
        mean_diff = abs(ko_values.mean() - wt_values.mean())
        diffs.append((tissue, mean_diff))
    else:
        print(f"{target_gene} not found in {tissue}")

# Sort tissues based on the absolute differences in TPM
sorted_tissues = [tissue for tissue, diff in sorted(diffs, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)]
sorted_expression_data = sorted(expression_data, key=lambda x: sorted_tissues.index(x['Tissue']))

# Convert sorted data to DataFrame
print("Sorting data and preparing for plotting...")
sorted_expression_df = pd.DataFrame(sorted_expression_data)

# Define colors for WT and KO
palette = {'WT': 'blue', 'KO': 'red'}

# Plotting boxplot with jitter using sorted tissues
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))
boxplot = sns.boxplot(data=sorted_expression_df, x='Tissue', y='TPM', hue='Condition',
                      palette=palette, order=sorted_tissues, hue_order=['WT', 'KO'], dodge=True)
sns.stripplot(data=sorted_expression_df, x='Tissue', y='TPM', hue='Condition',
              order=sorted_tissues, dodge=True, color=".25", jitter=True, hue_order=['WT', 'KO'])

# Customize plot
plt.title(f'Expression of {target_gene} in WT and KO across Tissues (Sorted by TPM Difference)', pad=20)
plt.ylabel('TPM')
plt.xlabel('Tissue')
sns.despine()
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)  # Subtle grid for y-axis

# Function to add p-value annotations with full scientific notation
def add_p_val_annotation(ax, x1, x2, y, p_val, h=0.02):
    exponent = int(np.floor(np.log10(p_val)))
    mantissa = p_val / (10**exponent)
    exponent_str = f"{exponent}".replace('-', '\u207B').translate(str.maketrans('0123456789','\u2070\u00B9\u00B2\u00B3\u2074\u2075\u2076\u2077\u2078\u2079'))
    p_text = f'p = {mantissa:.2f} x 10{exponent_str}'
    ax.plot([x1, x1, x2, x2], [y, y + h, y + h, y], color='k')
    ax.text((x1 + x2) * .5, y + h * 1.2, p_text, ha='center', va='bottom', color='k')

# Add p-values to the plot
positions = {tissue: pos for pos, tissue in enumerate(sorted_tissues)}
grouped = sorted_expression_df.groupby('Tissue')

# Adjust the positions for p-value annotations
for tissue, group in grouped:
    wt_pos = positions[tissue] - 0.2
    ko_pos = positions[tissue] + 0.2
    max_height = max(group['TPM'])
    add_p_val_annotation(boxplot, wt_pos, ko_pos, max_height, p_values[tissue], h=max_height * 0.1)

# Create custom legend
handles = [
    plt.Line2D([0], [0], color='blue', marker='o', linestyle='', label='Wild-Type', markersize=8),
    plt.Line2D([0], [0], color='red', marker='o', linestyle='', label='Knockout', markersize=8)
]
plt.legend(title='Condition', handles=handles, loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.15, 1))  # Position legend outside

plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('Zfp36l2_expression_across_tissues.svg', bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

print("Plot saved as 'Zfp36l2_expression_across_tissues.svg' and displayed successfully.")

# Import libraries



import pandas as pd

import seaborn as sns

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import matplotlib.patches as mpatches



# Load data files (ensure path is correct or files are in the same directory as your notebook)

bm_df = pd.read_csv('BM_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

kidney_df = pd.read_csv('Kidney_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

liver_df = pd.read_csv('Liver_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

lung_df = pd.read_csv('Lung_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

ovary_df = pd.read_csv('Ovary_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')

spleen_df = pd.read_csv('Spleen_Differential_expression_analysis_table.csv')



# Define the gene name you are interested in

target_gene = 'Zfp36l2'



# Extract TPM information for Zfp36L2

tissues = ['Bone Marrow', 'Kidney', 'Liver', 'Lung', 'Ovary', 'Spleen']

dfs = [bm_df, kidney_df, liver_df, lung_df, ovary_df, spleen_df]



expression_data = []



for tissue, df in zip(tissues, dfs):

    gene_data = df[df['Gene.name'] == target_gene]

    if not gene_data.empty:

        ko_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'KO' in col]

        wt_columns = [col for col in gene_data.columns if 'WT' in col]



        for col in ko_columns:

            expression_data.append({

                'Tissue': tissue,

                'Condition': 'KO',

                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]

            })



        for col in wt_columns:

            expression_data.append({

                'Tissue': tissue,

                'Condition': 'WT',

                'TPM': gene_data[col].values[0]

            })

    else:

        print(f"{target_gene} not found in {tissue}")



expression_df = pd.DataFrame(expression_data)



# Combine Tissue and Condition into a single column for better x-axis separation

expression_df['Tissue_Condition'] = expression_df['Tissue'] + ' (' + expression_df['Condition'] + ')'



# Compute median TPM for each Tissue_Condition and sort by it

median_tpm = expression_df.groupby('Tissue_Condition')['TPM'].median().sort_values(ascending=False)

sorted_tissue_conditions = median_tpm.index



# Define tissue colors

tissue_colors = {

    'Bone Marrow': 'brown',

    'Kidney': 'yellow',

    'Liver': 'purple',

    'Lung': 'blue',

    'Ovary': 'pink',

    'Spleen': 'green'

}

# Create a dictionary mapping Tissue_Condition to their respective colors

tissue_condition_colors = {tc: tissue_colors[tc.split(' (')[0]] for tc in sorted_tissue_conditions}



# Set the order of x-ticks based on median TPM values

plt.figure(figsize=(18, 8))

sns.boxplot(data=expression_df, x='Tissue_Condition', y='TPM', order=sorted_tissue_conditions, palette=tissue_condition_colors)

sns.stripplot(data=expression_df, x='Tissue_Condition', y='TPM', order=sorted_tissue_conditions, color=".25", jitter=True)



# Customize plot

plt.title('Expression of Zfp36l2 in WT and KO across Tissues')

plt.ylabel('TPM')

plt.xlabel('Tissue (Condition)')

sns.despine()



# Create a legend manually

handles = [mpatches.Patch(color=color, label=tissue) for tissue, color in tissue_colors.items()]

plt.legend(handles=handles, title="Tissue", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1), loc='upper right')



# Show plot

plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')

plt.tight_layout()



# Save as SVG file

plt.savefig('Zfp36l2_expression_across_tissues.svg')

plt.show()
